ase of the human heart, saying more than one feels.\n\n- Albert\n|\nFind Meaning, Find Yourself.\n\n- Diana Dentinger, Modus Vivendi: Your Life Your Way\n|\nThe Saviour, sacrifice his life as offering for sin.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nArvandus!' I tried again to reach him. 'You can come back now. I'm alone and would love to argue with you again.\n\n- J.M. Hackman, Spark\n|\nThere are days we all live with defensive thoughts in our mind. Without losing these thoughts we can’t totally be ourselves, and enjoy life's freedom of the heart.\n\n- Ron\n|\nDear me! how happy and good we'd be, if we had no worries!\n\n- Louisa May Alcott, Little Women\n|\nFreedom is not the absence of commitments, but the ability to choose - and commit myself to - what is best for me.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Zahir\n|\nGreat minds have purpose, others have wishes. Little minds are tamed and subdued by misfortunes; but great minds rise above them.\n\n- Washington\n|\nOne says the things which one feels the need to say, and which the other will not understand: one speaks for oneself alone.\n\n- Marcel\n|\nShe shot out of her seat, tired of waiting, at last ready to create her future.\n\n- Scott\n|\nBelief isn't supposed to make sense, at least not all the time. In that, it finds its power. It gets to creep up on you and carry you forward. Until you can carry yourself again.\n\n- Laura Dave, The Divorce Party\n|\nIf a rat is a good model for your emotional life, you're in big trouble.\n\n- Robert\n|\nYou see, to find the brightest wisdom one must pass through the darkest zones. And through the darkest zones there can be no guide. No guide, that is, but courage\n\n- Adam Gidwitz, A Tale Dark & Grimm\n|\nWhen I knew people, I knew me and when I knew me, I knew people.\n\n- Mahrukh\n|\nWhen ill luck begins, it does not come in sprinkles, but in showers.\n\n- Mark Twain, Pudd'nhead Wilson\n|\nOut of the fires of refinement, come the praise of His magnificence, the brilliance of His glory, and the honor of His 